HEADWORD: Glenoid
<hw>Gle"noid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/ socket
of a joint + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form; cf. F.
<ets>gl⟦eacute⟧no⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having
the form of a smooth and shallow depression; socketlike; -- applied to
several articular surfaces of bone; <as>as, the <ex>glenoid</ex> cavity,
or fossa, of the scapula, in which the head of the humerus
articulates</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glenoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
